Pre-Game Insights: The Boston Celtics enter the game as the No. 2 team in the Eastern Conference, while the Oklahoma City Thunder are atop the Western Conference with a franchise-record 14-game winning streak.
The Celtics are on a three-game winning streak, including a 54-point blowout of the Toronto Raptors and a 23-point win over the Houston Rockets.
The Thunder recently staged a comeback win against the New York Knicks, overcoming a 14-point deficit to claim a 117-107 victory and extend their winning streak to 14 games.
OKC’s success is driven by Shai Gilgeous-Alexander, who delivered 33 points and seven assists in their latest win.
The Thunder lead the league in net rating (12.1), anchored by their top-ranked defense (102.9 defensive rating), and remain unbeaten against Eastern Conference opponents.
Predicted starting lineups for the Thunder include Shai Gilgeous-Alexander, Cason Wallace, Lu Dort, Jalen Williams, and Isaiah Hartenstein.
Predicted starting lineups for the Celtics include Derrick White, Jrue Holiday, Sam Hauser, Jayson Tatum, and Kristaps Porzingis.
